comments.message:
stable players are gonna get less pp for the same play than if they played on stable due to no slider head accuracy and stricter notelock. the latter of which will also make passing maps far more difficult since it's a lot more likely that you'll either fail the map or get a terrible score from a choke
so basically stable players are getting punished when they could've kept slider pp out of the equation. sure, that's a bit scuffed but at least it keeps it more fair for stable players.
or they could've done the unthinkable of adding a lazer mod to stable which changes notelock and sliders to match lazer. that way people won't flip flop between both clients to set scores with better acc, score or pp.
